final_output_text: To underline text in OneNote, you can follow these steps:

1. First, locate the text you wish to underline. This can be done by scrolling through your notes or using the search function to find the specific text you're looking for.
2. Once you've found the text, right-click on it. This will bring up a context menu with various options.
3. From the context menu, click on the "B" button. This button is located at the top of the screen and is used to underline the selected text.
4. Alternatively, you can also underline text by first highlighting it. To do this, click and drag your mouse over the text to select it. Then, click on the "U" button, which is also located at the top of the screen.
5. After selecting the "B" or "U" button, the text will be underlined.

