final_output_text: To make a PB&J, the correct approach is to spread peanut butter on one side of the bread and jelly on the other side. This is because the classic PB&J sandwich typically consists of peanut butter and jelly, with the two ingredients separated by the bread. 

Here's a step-by-step explanation of the reasoning:

1. Start by taking two slices of bread. 
2. Spread a layer of peanut butter on one slice of bread. This is the traditional PB part of the PB&J.
3. Spread a layer of jelly on the other slice of bread. This is the traditional J part of the PB&J.
4. Place the two slices of bread together, with the peanut butter side facing the jelly side. This allows the peanut butter and jelly to be in contact with each other, creating the classic PB&J sandwich.

