1. **Solution 0:** This solution involves picking up the receiver, typing in the desired phone number, and then placing the receiver back onto the phone holder to talk. This method is incorrect because placing the receiver back onto the phone holder would not allow the caller to hear the person on the other end of the line. The receiver needs to be placed against the ear to facilitate communication.

2. **Solution 1:** This solution involves picking up the receiver, typing in the desired phone number, and then placing the receiver to your head to talk. This method is correct because placing the receiver against the ear allows the caller to hear the person on the other end of the line, enabling a two-way conversation.

Based on the analysis, the correct solution is the one that allows for effective communication by placing the receiver against the ear.

